"n. 祈求，诅咒 【英】 n. 咒语，诅咒(a curse) 【记】 im(坏)+prec(祷告)+a tion→祷告坏事→诅 咒; 【同】 参考：deprecate(反 对，抗议) n. 咒语; 诅咒(祈求降祸于某人) = curse 【记】im坏, prec = pray(v 祈祷; 恳求), ation－坏祈祷－诅咒 【参】deprecate(vt 抗议; 藐视) 【记】im 不好的 + precat 源自pray 祷告，祷告不好的事情发生；im + appreciate 感谢→不感谢→诅咒 【相关】deprecate(祷告以反对) 抗议, 不赞成, 反对 imprecation (n.)  mid-15c., ""a curse, cursing,"" from Latin imprecationem (nominative imprecatio), from past participle stem of imprecari ""invoke, pray, call down upon,"" from assimilated form of in- ""into, in, within"" (see in- (2)) + precari ""to pray, ask, beg, request"" (see pray). ""Current limited sense is characteristic of human nature."" [Weekley]"
